"2. Implementing supplementary 2.1 Intervention modes according feeding programmes to SFP objectives\n\n# IMPLEMENTING SUPPLEMENTARY FEEDING PROGRAMMES\n\n# INTERVENTION MODES ACCORDING TO SFP OBJECTIVES\nSFPs can pursue the following objectives in crisis situations:\n9 temporarily containing malnutrition, morbidity and mortality; 9 contributing to a more effective response to moderate malnutrition; 9 providing a safety net; 9 providing a relay for therapeutic feeding. The following recommendations relate to targeting, admission criteria according to targeting, and distribution modes for each scenario."